{"word":"πλαστός","slug":"πλαστός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πλαστός</b></el> <el>(πλαστός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πλάσσω'><el>πλάσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>formed, moulded</i> in clay or wax, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>fabricated, forged, counterfeit</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>πλαστός</el> a <i>supposititious</i> son, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}